In this tutorial, you'll learn how to access Kimi models using the OpenAI SDK through Puter's OpenAI-compatible endpoint. No Moonshot AI API key needed, just your Puter auth token.

## Prerequisites

- A [Puter](https://puter.com/) account
- Your Puter auth token, go to [puter.com/dashboard](https://puter.com/dashboard#account) and click **Copy** to get your auth token

![Puter copy auth token](https://developer.puter.com/assets/img/copy-auth-token.webp)

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) installed on your machine

## Setup

Install the OpenAI SDK:

```undefined
npm install openai
```

Then configure the client with Puter's base URL and your auth token:

```javascript
import OpenAI from "openai";

const client = new OpenAI({
  baseURL: "https://api.puter.com/puterai/openai/v1/",
  apiKey: "YOUR_PUTER_AUTH_TOKEN",
});
```

Replace `YOUR_PUTER_AUTH_TOKEN` with the auth token you copied from your Puter dashboard. That's all you need. No Moonshot AI API key required.

## Basic Chat Completion

Here's a simple chat completion using Kimi K2:

```javascript
import OpenAI from "openai";

const client = new OpenAI({
  baseURL: "https://api.puter.com/puterai/openai/v1/",
  apiKey: "YOUR_PUTER_AUTH_TOKEN",
});

const response = await client.chat.completions.create({
  model: "moonshotai/kimi-k2",
  messages: [\
    { role: "user", content: "What is the capital of France?" },\
  ],
});

console.log(response.choices[0].message.content);
```

Sample output:

```python
The capital of France is Paris.
```

The code is identical to what you'd write for OpenAI directly. The only difference is the base URL and the model string.

## Streaming

For longer responses, enable streaming to get results in real-time:

```javascript
import OpenAI from "openai";

const client = new OpenAI({
  baseURL: "https://api.puter.com/puterai/openai/v1/",
  apiKey: "YOUR_PUTER_AUTH_TOKEN",
});

const stream = await client.chat.completions.create({
  model: "moonshotai/kimi-k2",
  messages: [\
    { role: "user", content: "Write a short story about a robot learning to paint." },\
  ],
  stream: true,
});

for await (const chunk of stream) {
  const content = chunk.choices[0]?.delta?.content;
  if (content) {
    process.stdout.write(content);
  }
}
```

Set `stream: true` and iterate over the chunks as they arrive. Each chunk contains a piece of the response that you can display immediately.

## Conclusion

That's it. You now have access to Kimi through the OpenAI SDK via Puter, no Moonshot AI API key needed. Swap the model string to use any [Kimi model](https://developer.puter.com/ai/moonshotai/), from the efficient Kimi Dev to the powerful Kimi K2.5, or any of the hundreds of other [AI models](https://developer.puter.com/ai/models/) available through Puter.

